pageContext.description: Half of blade and most of the socket missing. Breaks are ancient. Within the socket is a small part of the wooden shaft. The pin is missing.
pageContext.patina: Green patina appears to have been partly removed by abrasion, probably workmen at pit.
pageContext.surface: Poor in patches. The edges are very battered and the upper part is bent.
pageContext.collection: Reading Museum 42:53,Donated by Chas. Prior and Son, gravel merchants.
pageContext.site: England, berkshire,bray,monkey island,river thames,probably found in dredgings by j.c.b. from near maidenhead bridge, dumped at monkey island.
